# Internationalization (i18n)

PRD §17 (Internationalization) · Epic [#197](https://github.com/mdg-labs/pipewatch/issues/197)

## Scope

- **In scope:** `apps/web` B-series dashboard UI (all user-visible copy, aria-labels, placeholders, empty/loading/error states).
- **Out of scope (MVP):** `apps/marketing` (English-only), API response bodies, worker logs.

## Source of truth

| Artifact | Path |
|---|---|
| Locale registry | `apps/web/src/i18n/supported-locales.json` |
| Message catalog | `apps/web/src/i18n/locales/{locale}.json` |
| Request config | `apps/web/src/i18n/request.ts` |

**Repo-JSON catalog only** — no Crowdin/Lokalise/external TMS in MVP. All strings live in git.

## Required pattern — `t()` for all user-facing copy

```tsx
import { useTranslations } from "next-intl";

const t = useTranslations("settings.apiKeys");
return <h1>{t("title")}</h1>;
```

Server components: `getTranslations` from `next-intl/server`.

**Every** user-visible string in `apps/web` TSX must resolve through the catalog — no inline English in JSX text, `aria-label`, `placeholder`, `title`, `alt`, or `label` attributes.

## Key naming

- Nested JSON, camelCase segments: `app.sidebar.dashboard`, `common.error.retry`.
- Group by feature/page namespace matching Page Inventory areas.
- ICU placeholders for interpolation and plurals: `{count, plural, one {# hour ago} other {# hours ago}}`.
- `defaultLocale` file (`en.json`) is canonical; other locales must have identical keys.

## `packages/ui` — prop-driven, no embedded copy

`packages/ui` is a **dumb presentation layer**. It accepts translated strings via props; it does not call `useTranslations` or ship English defaults for product copy.

```tsx
// ✅ packages/ui — caller supplies label
<Button aria-label={ariaLabel}>{children}</Button>

// ✅ apps/web — resolves copy
const t = useTranslations("common");
<Button aria-label={t("error.retry")}>{t("error.retry")}</Button>

// ❌ packages/ui — hardcoded product copy
<span>Loading...</span>
```

Grandfathered files listed in `I18N_HARDCODED_UI_ALLOWLISTED_FILES` (`scripts/i18n-check-hardcoded.ts`) are being migrated — **do not add new allowlist entries** for new work.

## CI commands (run locally on frontend copy changes)

```bash
pnpm i18n:validate          # key parity, non-empty values, locale registry alignment
pnpm i18n:check:hardcoded # scan apps/web + packages/ui for English literals
pnpm test:scripts           # unit tests for i18n scripts
```

These run in CI after unit tests (`.github/workflows/ci.yml`). Failures block merge.

## Adding strings

1. Add key to `apps/web/src/i18n/locales/en.json` under the correct namespace.
2. Use `t("key")` in component — never the English text directly.
3. Run `pnpm i18n:validate && pnpm i18n:check:hardcoded` before commit.

## Adding a locale

1. Extend `supported-locales.json` → `locales` array.
2. Add `locales/{code}.json` with full key parity to `en.json`.
3. `pnpm i18n:validate` must pass.
4. Wire locale selection in `request.ts` when product supports it.

## Forbidden

- Hardcoded user-facing English in new `apps/web` or `packages/ui` TSX (outside allowlist).
- New English defaults inside `packages/ui` for labels, badges, empty states, or chart legends.
- Keys in non-`defaultLocale` files that are missing from `en.json`.
- Empty catalog values.
- Scattered locale checks — use `isAppLocale` / `supported-locales.json`, not ad-hoc string compares.

## Verifier note

Frontend tasks (`domain:frontend`) must pass i18n CI commands when TSX or locale JSON changes. Docs-only tasks exempt.
